## Verification Checklist — Must Pass Before Every Handoff

Run through every item below in order. All items must pass. Document any failures and fix
before submitting.

### 1. Clean Build

```bash
# Remove all cached layers and volumes, build from scratch
docker-compose down -v --remove-orphans
docker-compose build --no-cache
```

- [ ] `docker-compose build --no-cache` exits with code `0`
- [ ] No `ERROR` lines in build output
- [ ] No use of `latest` tag appears in any build output

### 2. Full Stack Starts

```bash
docker-compose up -d
sleep 30  # allow start_period for health checks
```

- [ ] All three containers reach status `healthy` (not `starting`, not `unhealthy`)
- [ ] `docker-compose ps` shows all services as `Up (healthy)`

```bash
# Verify all healthy
docker-compose ps | grep -v "healthy" | grep -v "Name"
# Output should be empty — any line here is a failure
```

### 3. Service Endpoint Checks

```bash
# Backend health endpoint
curl -f http://localhost:8000/health
# Expected: HTTP 200 with JSON body

# Backend repos endpoint (core feature)
curl -f http://localhost:8000/repos
# Expected: HTTP 200 with JSON array of repositories

# Frontend loads
curl -f http://localhost:3000/
# Expected: HTTP 200 with HTML body
```

- [ ] `GET /health` returns `200`
- [ ] `GET /repos` returns `200` with a non-empty JSON array
- [ ] `GET localhost:3000/` returns `200`

### 4. Database Connectivity

```bash
docker exec portfolio_db pg_isready -U ${POSTGRES_USER} -d ${POSTGRES_DB}
```

- [ ] Output includes `accepting connections`
- [ ] Backend logs show successful DB connection on startup (no `FATAL` or `connection refused`)

### 5. GitHub API Cache Behavior

```bash
# First request — should hit GitHub API and populate cache
curl -f http://localhost:8000/repos

# Second request — should return cached data from Postgres
curl -f http://localhost:8000/repos
```

- [ ] Both requests return `200`
- [ ] Backend logs confirm cache hit on second request (no second GitHub API call)
- [ ] `docker logs portfolio_backend` contains no `rate limit` errors

### 6. Non-Root User Verification

```bash
docker exec portfolio_backend whoami
docker exec portfolio_frontend whoami
```

- [ ] Neither service returns `root`

### 7. No Secrets Leaked

```bash
# Inspect built images for secrets
docker inspect portfolio_backend | grep -i "token\|password\|secret"
docker inspect portfolio_frontend | grep -i "token\|password\|secret"
```

- [ ] No real secret values appear in image inspect output
- [ ] `.env` file is not present inside any container:

```bash
docker exec portfolio_backend ls /app/.env 2>&1 | grep "No such file"
docker exec portfolio_frontend ls /app/.env 2>&1 | grep "No such file"
```

### 8. Clean Shutdown and Restart

```bash
docker-compose down
docker-compose up -d
sleep 30
docker-compose ps
```

- [ ] All services return to `healthy` after restart with no manual intervention
- [ ] Postgres data persists across restart (named volume preserved)

### 9. Log Sanity Check

```bash
docker-compose logs --no-color 2>&1 | grep -iE "error|exception|traceback|fatal" \
  | grep -v "healthcheck"
```

- [ ] Output is empty or contains only expected/ignorable startup messages
- [ ] No Python tracebacks in backend logs
- [ ] No Next.js build errors in frontend logs

### 10. Final Gate

```bash
docker-compose down -v --remove-orphans
docker-compose up --build --abort-on-container-exit
```

- [ ] Process exits with code `0`
- [ ] All services started and remained healthy until `--abort-on-container-exit` triggered by
  natural completion (or no exit at all, meaning all containers are running)

**If any item in this checklist fails, the handoff does not happen.**